<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880108-0107 </DOCNO><HL> Sentencing of David Clark Is Delayed Unitl Jan. 22 </HL><SO> </SO><CO> DJ </CO><IN> PUB STK SCR </IN><G> JUS </G><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sentencing was delayed until Jan. 22 for David W.C. Clark, a lawyer involved in an insider-trading scheme using Wall Street Journal stories in 1983 and 1984.    Mr. Clark, a former partner in the New York law firm of Appleton, Rice andamp; Perrin, was found guilty in November in federal court in Manhattan of embezzling about $3.7 million from clients to invest in stocks.    Sentencing was originally set for yesterday. </TEXT></DOC>